				<h1>About Our Project</h1>
				
				<div class="content-section">
					<h2>Project Overview</h2>
					<p>
						The 42 Webserv project is a complete HTTP server implementation developed in C++ as part of the 42 School curriculum.
						Our server handles multiple client connections simultaneously, processes HTTP requests, and serves appropriate responses
						while strictly adhering to RFC standards.
					</p>
				</div>
				
				<h2>Project Components</h2>
				<p>The server is composed of several key components working together:</p>
				
				<div class="project-components">
					<div class="component-card">
						<h3><span>ğŸ”Œ</span> Socket Management</h3>
						<p>
							Implements non-blocking socket operations using poll() for handling multiple connections efficiently.
							Includes IP address parsing, port binding, and connection queuing.
						</p>
					</div>
					
					<div class="component-card">
						<h3><span>ğŸ“</span> Configuration Parser</h3>
						<p>
							Reads and validates server configuration files with support for multiple servers, routes,
							error pages, and CGI settings. Handles both JSON and custom configuration formats.
						</p>
					</div>
					
					<div class="component-card">
						<h3><span>ğŸ“¨</span> Request Parser</h3>
						<p>
							Parses incoming HTTP requests including headers, body, and chunked transfer encoding.
							Validates request syntax according to RFC 7230 standards.
						</p>
					</div>
					
					<div class="component-card">
						<h3><span>ğŸ“¤</span> Response Generator</h3>
						<p>
							Constructs proper HTTP responses with status codes, headers, and body content.
							Handles both static file serving and dynamic content generation.
						</p>
					</div>
					
					<div class="component-card">
						<h3><span>âš™ï¸</span> CGI Handler</h3>
						<p>
							Implements CGI 1.1 specification with support for multiple interpreters (Python, PHP, Perl).
							Manages environment variables, standard I/O streams, and timeout control.
						</p>
					</div>
					
					<div class="component-card">
						<h3><span>ğŸ§ª</span> Testing Framework</h3>
						<p>
							Comprehensive test suite including unit tests, integration tests, and performance benchmarks.
							Automated testing with custom client implementations.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				
				<h2>Technical Specifications</h2>
				<div class="content-section">
					<ul>
						<li><strong>Language:</strong> C++98 (with some C++11 features where allowed)</li>
						<li><strong>Concurrency:</strong> Single-process, event-driven architecture</li>
						<li><strong>Protocols:</strong> HTTP/1.1 (RFC 7230-7235)</li>
						<li><strong>Supported Methods:</strong> GET, POST, DELETE, HEAD</li>
						<li><strong>Configuration:</strong> Multiple servers with different host:port combinations</li>
						<li><strong>Performance:</strong> Handles 1000+ concurrent connections on modern hardware</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
				
